org.fluidity.composition.container.spi

Interface DependencyGraph.Traversal

  • Enclosing interface:
    DependencyGraph

    public static interface DependencyGraph.Traversal
    Maintains, during dependency graph traversal, state such as nodes and component contexts along a dependency path.

    Usage

    You don't interact with an internal interface.

    • Method Detail

      • follow

        DependencyGraph.Node follow(Object identity,
                            Class<?> api,
                            ContextDefinition context,
                            Supplier<DependencyGraph.Node> reference)
        Follows a dependency reference. This is an indirectly recursive method as during resolution of a node further invocations of this method are expected and thus one single traversal instance is able to maintain a path of invocations.
        Parameters:
        identity - identifies the reference; used to detect circular references.
        api - the component interface the dependency refers to.
        context - the component context at the dependency reference.
        reference - the node reference that can resolve the graph node that the dependency leads to.
        Returns:
        the resolved node.

      • observed

        DependencyGraph.Traversal observed(ComponentContainer.Observer... observers)
        Returns a new instance, one that invokes the given observers in addition to invoking the observer this instance already has. The returned traversal will keep maintaining the same path as the one handling this method call.
        Parameters:
        observers - the observers to invoke.
        Returns:
        the new traversal.

      • instantiating

        void instantiating(Class<?> type)
        Notifies the traversal's observer, if any, about the actual class of the object being instantiated.
        Parameters:
        type - the class of the object being instantiated.

      • instantiated

        Object instantiated(Class<?> type,
                    Object component)
        Notifies the traversal's observer, if any, about the instantiation of the given type. See ComponentContainer.Observer.instantiated() for details.

        Note: the receiver will not call any method on the instantiated object while executing this method.

        Parameters:
        type - the type just instantiated.
        component - the component that has just been instantiated.
        Returns:
        the component.

      • path

        DependencyPath path()
        Returns the current resolution or instantiation path.
        Returns:
        the current resolution or instantiation path.
